      <h3 class="accom-heading">&#127984; About the Palazzo</h3>
      <p class="accom-text">Palazzo Mannocchi is an 18th-century castle property in the heart of Petritoli village. It has frescoed ceilings, vaulted halls from the Roman period, period furniture, and panoramic views of the sea and mountains. The place takes up nearly a quarter of the village center — it's massive and beautiful and a little wild.</p>
      <p class="accom-text">It has 40 bedrooms, 19 bathrooms, 9 kitchens, grand salons, terraces, balconies, a rose garden, two swimming pools, and a large jacuzzi. There's WiFi throughout, including the bedrooms. And with the village right outside the door, you won't need a car for anything during the week.</p>
