      <h3 class="accom-heading">&#128719; What to Expect</h3>
      <p class="accom-text">We want to be upfront: <strong>this is not a hotel</strong>. It's a charming, centuries-old property — think cozy slumber party in an Italian castle, not a resort. Bathrooms and common areas are shared, we'll be looking after ourselves, and the furniture is antique (read: character, not concierge).</p>
      <p class="accom-text">The palazzo is divided so that different groups — couples, families, friends — can have their own private bedrooms, suites, or even entire floors, while sharing the communal spaces like salons, pool terraces, and balconies. You'll have your own space to retreat to, but the best part is being together.</p>
